<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-02-19T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-02-19T20:00:00-05:00" n="58" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d58">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">821.51/2591: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Colombia</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Braden</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-02-19T20:00:00-05:00">February 19, 1941—8
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>48. Your despatch no. 1335, February 3, 1941. Please indicate to the
                            Department in as much detail as is readily available what types of
                            public works projects the Colombian Government may wish to carry out
                            with Export-Import Bank assistance within the next 2 or 3 years.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>